The Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board (JAMB) has declared as false rumours that the results of the Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination conducted on Saturday, March 15, Monday, March 16 and Tuesday, March 17, 2020 had been cancelled. In a press statement signed by JAMB’s head of media, Dr Fabian Benjamin, the board urged candidates who took the examinations to disregard the rumours, adding that they could check their results by sending ‘RESULT’ to 55019 and not from the board’s website. He said: “The results of the first day was placed on the website and some fraudulent individuals were coping and manipulating it to deceive unsuspecting candidates hence our decision to move it to the mobile platform for candidates to use their unique phone numbers used in registering for the examination to access their results.” JAMB also revealed that it has continuously released results of the exam, a day after, adding that the result of the over 450,000 candidates who sat for the examination on Tuesday, March 20, would be released before 12 noon Wednesday (yesterday). “We urge the public to always cross check information provided on social media. Results of the examination will continue to be released as examinations are taken. In a few days from now, we will be concluding the 2020 exercise and we urge all candidates to be vigilant as many fraudsters who couldn’t operate successfully given the security measures put in place to secure our system will want to use every opportunity of information gap to defraud or mislead unsuspecting candidates,” JAMB said.